comments: The course is a seminar with visiting professors presenting their working papers. It is intellectually stimulating, but does not follow a typical class schedule. I did not answer some of the evaluation questions because of this disjunction.
The course consists of attendance at seminars by outside and internal speakers, and as such many of the questions are not applicable to this specific course.
Exposure to a wide variety of current research in environmental and resource economics.

narratives.question_text: The things about this course most in need of improvement are:

comments: A great complement to the theory from other classes. Very interesting to see current research in environmental and resource economics.
Since it provides up-to-date information about current research in environmental and resource economics, this course is very important for my overall program.
